A 25-year-old man has been arrested after he allegedly murdered his mother in Dutywa, in the Eastern Cape, police said on Friday. Police spokesperson Jackson Manatha said the 57-year-old woman went to the local clinic on Tuesday, where she reported that she was injured by her son. Manatha said the woman subsequently passed away at the clinic. Her son was arrested on Wednesday. The motive for the murder was not known. The man is expected to appear in the Ngqamakhwe Magistrateâ€™s Court on Friday.